caption: D style food and for a reasonably affordable price considering it’s the Upper West Side. Nearby baseball field, soccer field, and sand pit keep the area busy and beaming with life. Has two levels, makes it slightly confusing, some more signs dictating where everything is. Decent food...what you would expect...except the pizza. The pizza is awful and an absolute disappointment. Nothing like what you’d expect, fair warning don’t have the pizza it’s awful. Besides that, everything is fine, don’t expect great food, great beer selection though.

Best thing about this spot is the view. It's not bad, but nothing too memorable about this place. They need to expand their menu and add heaters as it gets colder. Some of this might be because of the pandemic, so hopefully it will be better as we recover

Simple, but great for what it is.  We just had beer and some apps with a great view of the Hudson and New Jersey.  Staff were all so friendly.  Too bad the are closing for the season at the end of October.

Enjoy while the weather is nice. If you're going to eat outside, you might as well enjoy the Riverside Park scenery here at "Hudon Beach." Quite an extensive and eclectic menu; not sure how they manage it with what appears to be a small kitchen, but they do. Service here is more like self-service: You order at the counter, pick it up when your number is called, and take it to back to a table of your choice. I will definitely return.
Okay for a quick bite.

You can't reserve tables - at peak times you have to stand around and be ready to pounce when someone leaves a table. The food is not wonderful. It's a very pleasant place to eat in good weather. And safe, out in the open air, in the age of coronavirus.
Beautiful setting,great food and friendly staff.Perfect day.
We have always loved Ellington, but the food was not up to snuff when we visited them in the park. We were sadly surprised..

We took our food to our table, 2 burgers and pizza not eaten yet along with our personal stuff on the table. I took my 7 year old daughter to the restroom for couple of minutes, we came back and our food and our personal stuff were taken from the table. When we went to get our stuff back an employee harassed me and my daughter and blamed us for going to the restroom.
Wonderful atmosphere with food and drinks. Good spot for the pandemic!

2020-0905.  I came here to plant some horseradish and use the bathroom after swimming in the Hudson, but have to say I'm so impressed at how well they are handling this covid thing.  They've spread out nicely, they have a great system for announcing your meal is ready.  And the bar looks open. Its likely the best place to bring your kids and there are now even more options for working out.  This time of year is fabulous.  Not too hot. Still sunny.  I hope they have a lot of days left.  It was very clean today.  Two years ago: First, I have to make it clear that I did not come here to hang out at Ellington in the park. I came here to look at my plantings and to swing on the Rings. I did both of those things. The amount of litter on the sand was somewhat depressing. This is a great place to bring your kids to and let them run wild on the sand. Just you might want to think about cleaning up after them maybe picking up their trash I may be a little bit of someone else's.

Had the fruit cup $10, friends had the $18 burger and the $15 beef sliders. The sliders were really tasty, and the burger was sizable and tasty as well. The tangerine in the fruit cup tasted kinda sour, and the mango was hard and had green edges. The kiwi slices were pretty good too. The party did order some drinks, which were described as good but expensive at ~$12+. There were canned beverages for $5

I only had sweet potatoes fries here and they were really good. There could not be a better setting, lots of trees, the breeze from the Hudson river and nuch more goodness around. The only thing that I did not like was the customer service. The cashier had an aptitud like I was asking for a favor or like I was asking for free food (maybe He wanted me to spend more 🧐 Who knows)

We have been here 2 times in the last month. We stopped here while riding on the trail. All the food we've had have been amazing. The buffalo wings, avocado toast, calamari, the park hamburger and margaritas and they all were good. The only thing I would suggest is a bit more tequila in those ritas.😉🍹

This is the kind of place you go to for the fresh air, location, maybe catch a nice sunset. You don’t go there for the quality of the food which is also way overpriced and the cheap liquor. It does well because as I said it’s location and lack of competition, but it would be a whole lot more popular if either it was more fairly priced or the quality of their offerings improved.

Great place in Riverside Park with even better views! Food is good and drink selection solid. Especially during COVID it’s awesome having local places in the community providing spaces for people to still spend time together and feel safe doing it!
Excellent outdoor summer spot with delicious bar-style food and drinks.
Spent money on food and drinks only to get chased away a min later in the rain...should’ve offered a refund at the least...

Love, love this place!  Especially in these times (Covid-19), it’s the perfect place to meet friends, have a bite, and a few drinks.  That’s exactly what I did with a few friends yesterday afternoon.  Let meet not forget, it was surprisingly very affordable.

If I could give 0 stars I would. Do not eat here. It’s terrible and the service is not great. They simply don’t care, keep walking!  Ps this is meant to be Avacado toast for $12, it tastes so bad!

Don’t get the fruit bowl - it said it’d come with kiwi, mango, papaya, pineapple, mint, other fun fruits, but it literally was mostly melons and cantaloupes with just a bit of pineapple and mango. Complete waste of $10.  Instead just get drinks and maybe one pizza to share if you get drunk. The staff is awesome and the drinks are good. Food is meh.

My running club works out near here and I love getting a beer after practice. Sometimes the kitchen is slow, and it's a little pricey. But you can't beat the view or the location. Especially nice during pandemic times with outside seating.

*July 2020 update* Thankfully Ellington in The Park was already set up well for Phase 2 Covid dining! They’ve spaced out their tables more to accommodate distancing and sanitize them between parties. Highly recommend for a summer night - and try the fig/goat cheese pizza, it’s big enough to share and delicious.  *2018* Great outdoor seating on the top and bottom levels, but top level is ideal as it’s way less noisy and more breezy, if you can snag a table (seat yourself- try to share a table with a smaller group if you’re just with 1 or 2 people). Drinks are good, especially in summer when they do frozen drinks and pitchers of rosé sangria. Food is pricey and fairly standard bar food, but with some good salad options and amazing fries and mini sliders.
Nice area.  Everyone spaced out properly and staff masked up. Great food and drink too.
nothing special. Overpriced mediocre bar food. Only the setting makes it tolerable. Bring your own food to the park and you can enjoy the view anywhere.

Ellington in the Park is that spot.  With a lovely view of the Hudson River, the soft hum of traffic on the Henry Hudson parkway, families riding by on bikes, the occasional raptor flying through the trees, you can feel the stress of the day falling away.

Terrible service and smelled awful  They ran out of almost very beer on their menu and then their credit card machine broke and we were stuck for over an hour trying to pay. Then they realized they could use the downstairs credit card machine. On top of this they were dumping the septic tank during dinner. This was the most absurd dining experience I have had in a couple years.  Food was decent, however the service and the septic smell left a bad taste in my mouth

Here, you really are mostly just paying for the environment and atmosphere. Came here for the first time with a pal to watch the sunset and grab a beer. There were a lot of people, but finding a spot to sit was surprisingly easy on a beautiful Friday evening. The environment is gorgeous: they had cool lights, lively music, families with kids running around and looking happy, and groups of people sitting around and chatting. From our seat we watched people working out in the park and of course enjoyed the beautiful sunset on the Hudson.  As far as being a restaurant though...not all that much was great. Service took a long time and there didn’t seem to be much organization. Further (as you probably know from other reviews) the place is just too pricy. My friend and I each got a $5 hot dog and a $7 can of beer which were their cheapest options. If you venture further into the menu, you’ll be paying a lot more. Lucky though we weren’t too hungry and just wanted a nice spot to watch the sunset and have a beer, which this place provided. I’ll probably be back for special occasions but couldn’t come regularly.
